Doctors Say Hospitals Are Stopping Them From Wearing MasksEnlarge this image toggle caption zoranm/Getty Images zoranm/Getty ImagesNeilly Buckalew is a traveling doctor who fills in at hospitals when there's need.
Many doctors, nurses and other hospital workers say they don't feel protected and are afraid in the midst of a shortage of masks and other protective gear.
Leaders at the American Academy of Emergency Medicine says they have heard accounts like Buckalew's from health care workers across the country.
A virus that causes a disease that has killed dozens of health care workers in Italy and already taken the lives of at least two health care workers at the epicenter of the spread in the New York City metro area.
Koch said protecting doctors has been his number one goal, even securing N95 masks to supply to hospitals that couldn't find any.